<body>
    <h1>Blitz Testing Daily Digest with Claude</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"029bdd03416a" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClau=
de-TL;DR">TL;DR</h2>
<p local-id=3D"74cfdf31122b">We experimented with using Claude Code plus va=
rious browser-driving tools (e.g. <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:=
//chromewebstore.google.com/detail/claude/fcoeoabgfenejglbffodgkkbkcdhcgfn"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Claude in Chrome</a>, the <a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://claude.com/plugins/chrome-devtools-mcp" rel=3D"nofollow">Chrome=
 DevTools plugin</a>, and <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://claude=
zilla.com/" rel=3D"nofollow">claudezilla</a>) to blitz test the new <a clas=
s=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/jira/polaris/project=
s/AGNT/ideas?selectedIssue=3DAGNT-82" rel=3D"nofollow">Daily Digest</a> fea=
ture. Claude was able to generate comprehensive test plans based on the act=
ual code and architecture and successfully (and mostly-autonomously) work t=
hrough the test cases in the Dev environment. It raised 13 bug findings (2 =
have been closed as wrong/duplicate as of this writing), many of which appe=
ar to be valid, though largely minor, as well as 4 tasks/improvements. It s=
truggled with mobile layouts, regardless of which browser-driving tool was =
used. Overall, it showed strong promise for automating a large amount of ro=
utine and exploratory testing, and we will be looking for ways to make this=
 flow a regular part of the Agentic=E2=80=99s tribe=E2=80=99s way of workin=
g.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"2155bf82dd3b" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Setup=
">Setup</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"7aff8304f71a" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Agent=
">Agent</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ceef557a1dc8">Claude Code, Opus 4.7, initiated <strong>above=
</strong> my local repos (e.g. in my <code>github/</code> directory) so tha=
t it can easily jump into the relevant repos (e.g. <code>mews-js</code> and=
 <code>agt-core</code>).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f25e5d8fd54a" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Brows=
erControl">Browser Control</h3>
<p local-id=3D"3aba6a0f3aa4"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://chr=
omewebstore.google.com/detail/claude/fcoeoabgfenejglbffodgkkbkcdhcgfn" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Claude in Chrome</a> plugin added to Edge in the first run. <=
a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://claude.com/plugins/chrome-devtool=
s-mcp" rel=3D"nofollow">Chrome DevTools plugin</a> in the second. You can a=
lso use the Playwright MCP, but I wanted to see if taking over an already-a=
uthenticated browser would be smoother. <a class=3D"confluence-userlink use=
r-mention" data-account-id=3D"712020:f0909273-d99e-43de-8f28-eb81b969785d" =
href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/people/712020:f0909273-d99e-43de-8f=
28-eb81b969785d?ref=3Dconfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=
=3D"967803253" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=
=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki">Violet Gall=
o</a> also had some success with <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:/=
/claudezilla.com/" rel=3D"nofollow">claudezilla</a>.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f74a1a00ba6f" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Promp=
t">Prompt</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Let's c=
ome up with a testing plan for "blitz testing" the daily digest feature. Yo=
u can explore the frontend in @mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/s=
rc/dailyDigest/ and the backend is=20
   in @agt-core. The idea is that it is a central place to show Smart Tasks=
 for consumption in the morning/at the start of the user's shift. Users can=
 filter on dates (up to 7 days from today),=20
   departments, guest status, and more. It should work on mobile (with a ti=
nder-like swipe interaction) as well as desktop. Ultimately, I want you to =
be able to interact with the feature       =20
  yourself via the browser. We should consider as many edge cases as we can=
. Start with a plan after you've understood the feature scope.</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"d9c0d4028120">Claude then explored the relevant files and di=
rectories (mentioned in the prompt above with the <code>@</code> symbol) to=
 gather an understanding of how the pieces actually work, from the FE behav=
iors to the backend API structures and responses. From there, it formulated=
 a plan for me to review.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"94fd39cb3bfe" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Promp=
tRefinement">Prompt Refinement</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8d5e81526b4c">Nate used the <a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://plannotator.ai/" rel=3D"nofollow">Plannotator</a> tool to give =
me an interactive version of Claude=E2=80=99s plan, which allows you to com=
ment on pieces, edit the plan, strike things through, etc.</p><span class=
=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedd=
ed-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" width=
=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"cc10b701108734478c9caa89739e612a40880b02b7=
1e86a040ea0bf7452ad747" data-image-src=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/d=
