- Notes: workaround, related findings, hypothesized cause
```

## Critical files (for reference while diagnosing)

- `mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/src/dailyDigest/DailyDigestPa=
ge.tsx`
- `mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/src/dailyDigest/usePendingAct=
ions.tsx`
- `mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/src/dailyDigest/SwipeableSugg=
estionCard.tsx`
- `mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/src/dailyDigest/filterAndSort=
Suggestions.ts`
- `mews-js/packages/commander/modules/agentic/src/dailyDigest/SuggestionDet=
ailPanel.tsx`
- `agt-core/agt_core/api/smart_tasks/router.py`

## Verification (how to know the session worked)

1. Browser is on the hosted dev Daily Digest page; either cards render OR a=
 correct empty/info state is shown.
2. Findings file exists with header populated. Zero findings is a valid res=
ult.
3. Tier 0 smoke is complete with results recorded for S1, S2, S3, D1, D2, F=
1, F7, F9, P1, P5, E5.
4. For each P0 row reached: either a "PASS" line in the findings file or a =
finding entry.
5. At least one accept and one reject mutation has been made-and-undone (U1=
) and made-and-committed (U2); browser network panel shows the matching `PO=
ST /smartTasks/{create,reject}` for U2 and absence for U1.
6. Pg1 produces a clear answer about pagination behavior (works / doesn't e=
xpose load-more / etc.) =E2=80=94 not just an observation.
7. N2 and N3 confirm the cache recovers from mutation failures.
8. Screenshots saved for any P0/P1 finding.

End-of-session note appended to findings: time spent per tier, what didn't =
get covered, what to follow up on next session.
</pre>
</div>
</div>
