<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># Daily=
 Digest Blitz Test Plan

**Epic:** [AGT-746](https://mews.atlassian.net/browse/AGT-746) =E2=80=94 Sm=
art Tasks: Daily Digest

## Environment

- **URL:** `https://app.mews-develop.com/Commander/9173ac0f-7f88-4f5b-8bba-=
b310006b0da0/DailyDigest`
- **Browser:** Firefox (regular mode, separate window via Claudezilla)
- **Auth:** Manual login required before automated testing begins
- **Tab ID:** 203 (Claudezilla handle)
- **Mobile testing:** `firefox_set_viewport` with device presets (iphone-14=
, ipad-mini, etc.)

## Key Constraints

- **Suggestions are scarce.** We don't control how many exist. Some dates (=
e.g., May 1) will have suggestions, others won't. Play with filters to find=
 them.
- **Accept/reject is permanent.** Each action permanently removes a suggest=
ion. Be conservative =E2=80=94 only accept/reject 1-2 to verify the flow + =
undo. Most testing is read-only (view, filter, sort).
- **Feature flags required.** Both `dailyDigestEnabled` and `opDailyDigestE=
nabled` must be on.

## Setup Steps

1. Claude creates a new Firefox window (regular mode, not private =E2=80=94=
 cookies must persist)
2. Claude navigates to the Daily Digest URL
3. **User authenticates manually** (login page redirect expected)
4. User confirms "ready" when on the Daily Digest page
5. Claude takes a screenshot to confirm state, then begins test execution

## Output Format

Each finding reported as:

&gt; **[SHORT TITLE]** =E2=80=94 Severity: `critical` | `high` | `medium` |=
 `low` | `info`
&gt;
&gt; _Longer description of what was observed, what was expected, and repro=
duction steps._

---

