<h2 local-id=3D"b2d31203629c" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Execu=
tion">Execution</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"d7724f10cf7e" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Frict=
ionPoints/Limitations">Friction Points/Limitations</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"29b81cfb93b9" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Resta=
rtingClaudetoEnableChrome">Restarting Claude to Enable Chrome</h4>
<p local-id=3D"5dd336f573a8">I had to restart my planning session because I=
 installed the Claude browser extension mid-session. I re-initalized with <=
code>claude --chrome</code> and then pointed it back at the plan.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"43a3e0c14bfe" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Signi=
ngInforClaude">Signing In for Claude</h4>
<p local-id=3D"7558da191a11">Initial authentication was a pain. Perhaps we =
could instruct Claude on how to sign in, but we did need to authenticate ma=
nually in order to unlock 1Password to get the credentials/otherwise sign i=
n. We are aware of alternatives to this flow in the Test environment with a=
 special user and token, which is not available with Dev at this time:</p><=
span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper conflue=
nce-embedded-manual-size"><a href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/downlo=
ad/attachments/1941537376/Screen%20Recording%202026-04-30%20at%201.55.32%E2=
%80%AFPM.mov?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1777575579811&amp;cacheVers=
ion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2">Screen Recording 2026-04-30 at 1.55.32=E2=80=AFPM.mov=
</a></span>
<h4 local-id=3D"d1ca1a622efd" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Takin=
gScreenshotsonWrongMonitor">Taking Screenshots on Wrong Monitor</h4>
<p local-id=3D"11db8f037f34">After Claude had finished running, it was aske=
d to create Jira bugs/tasks for its findings and link them to our Epic. Tha=
t part went fine, no problems. However, it struggled to take screenshots, e=
ither mistiming the moment or taking screenshots of the wrong monitor. All =
relatively easy to fix.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"0e6e4508c1d8" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-NotEx=
ecutingFullPlan">Not Executing Full Plan</h4>
<p local-id=3D"5c1959268fd3">The initial plan had some cases outside of the=
 test matrix that were meant to be edge cases for testing. The initial runs=
 showed Claude mis-interpreting these as guidance and not test cases. Subse=
quent runs incorporated the testable elements into discrete test cases in t=
he matrix.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d740071ebe33" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Execu=
tionItself">Execution Itself</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c108a96ade84">After addressing the friction points above, Cl=
aude was able to drive the test cases via the browser. In this example, you=
 can see that it had opened the date picker and in the Claude session it no=
tes that test cases are passing (at the time of this screenshot):</p><span =
class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-e=
mbedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" =
width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"68060d59ac68852974c07919177d7498e4ef8=
6ec0fc5245649eabaf8ddefb24d" data-image-src=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/w=
iki/download/attachments/1941537376/Screenshot%202026-04-30%20at%202.01.40%=
E2%80%AFPM.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1777575836542&amp;cacheVe=
rsion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"1430" data-width=3D"2558" data-unres=
olved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1941865114" data-linke=
d-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-link=
ed-resource-default-alias=3D"Screenshot 2026-04-30 at 2.01.40=E2=80=AFPM.pn=
g" data-base-url=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-c=
ontent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1941537376" =
data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"7" data-media-id=3D"55fe99fa-ff11=
-43c8-a213-71eabbd3c0b8" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"261"></span>
<p local-id=3D"18a3635aff2b">This recording shows Claude autonomously contr=
olling the authenticated browser window, interacting with elements, and dec=
iding whether the test case passed or failed (increase the playback speed):=
</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper co=
nfluence-embedded-manual-size"><a href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/d=
ownload/attachments/1941537376/Screen%20Recording%202026-04-30%20at%202.16.=
00%E2%80%AFPM.mov?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1777577048776&amp;cach=
eVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2">Screen Recording 2026-04-30 at 2.16.00=E2=80=AFP=
M.mov</a></span>
<p local-id=3D"ceb50b42146a">This recording shows Claude again autonomously=
 controlling the browser window. This time, it is using the <a class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" href=3D"https://claude.com/plugins/chrome-devtools-mcp" rel=3D"=
nofollow">Chrome DevTools plugin</a>, which is more powerful than the <a cl=
ass=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/clau=
de/fcoeoabgfenejglbffodgkkbkcdhcgfn" rel=3D"nofollow">Claude in Chrome</a> =
plugin (specifically it=E2=80=99s able to use DevTools to turn on mobile vi=
ews rather than just shrinking the window to a =E2=80=9Cmobile=E2=80=9D siz=
e) but, notably, it does not work well with Edge. So, we still needed to ma=
nually authenticate the user (in a Chromium window) and navigate to the rig=
ht page before letting Claude run (increase the playback speed):</p><span c=
lass=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-em=
bedded-manual-size"><a href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/download/att=
