<h2 local-id=3D"d1689a712cf5" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Findi=
ngsFromThisExperiment">Findings From This Experiment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a6d3e8f99cfb">In no particular order, here are some thoughts=
 and findings from this experiment. For actual bugs discovered, look at <a =
data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/x/9=
wG0cw" local-id=3D"f5dfc03ae4dd" rel=3D"nofollow">https://mews.atlassian.ne=
t/wiki/x/9wG0cw</a> (under my name, <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-me=
ntion" data-account-id=3D"712020:b47d50d6-4d25-488e-be7b-c40040985fc7" href=
=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki/people/712020:b47d50d6-4d25-488e-be7b-c=
40040985fc7?ref=3Dconfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=3D"=
967835656" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"=
userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://mews.atlassian.net/wiki">Nathaniel Goeth=
el</a>):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"05dca17cd643">
<li local-id=3D"c37b9a3e5d81">
<p local-id=3D"cf1e8575e04e">Overall, running the test suite took 30-45 min=
utes. The vast majority of this was completely autonomous. No manual interv=
ention was required (outside of the inital friction points described above)=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9edfe78fe020">
<p local-id=3D"fd9a1c793e70">Claude was able to manuever on the page and se=
t things up so it could continue testing. For example, when you have the fi=
lter panel open and shrink the browser to mobile size, the filter panel sta=
y open, blocking the cards. This isn=E2=80=99t a common case for users (the=
y=E2=80=99ll either be on desktop OR mobile, not resizing their browser win=
dow down to mobile), Claude was able to identify that, close the window, an=
d move on. Tools like Playwright would have failed here, or required defens=
ive logic to account for this. This ability to =E2=80=9Cself-heal=E2=80=9D =
is significant.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eba623e385ac">
<p local-id=3D"3c6684e31382">Even with the Chrome DevTools plugin, Claude w=
as still unable to trigger the mobile UI. This is easily done manually via =
DevTools, so more exploration there is warranted.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a28cef429ecc">
<p local-id=3D"58610882c5de">Authenticating Claude is the biggest pain poin=
t. Consider adding test users with less-sensitive credentials that can be q=
uickly accessed by Claude for fully autonomous testing.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2586e049563d">
<p local-id=3D"f9e874a4a76e">Claude was very capable of deriving test cases=
 (happy paths and not-so-happy paths) as long as it had the ability to inve=
stigate the code that undergirds the feature.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"37d4a24f45cf">
<p local-id=3D"54885e4ba1d6">The Plannotator tool is incredibly useful and =
a much better DX than the vanilla Claude planning process. Highly recommend=
ed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cf1f63c18d77">
<p local-id=3D"eca7e31fec19">This is still AI, and it can still make mistak=
es. Some initial bug reports have been closed as impossible or unreproducib=
le.</p></li>
</ul>
