</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e0bd006d-7c60-4634-b332-da3f92c9f05b">
<p local-id=3D"1f8544b7152d">Environment: hosted Mews develop (<a class=3D"=
external-link" href=3D"https://app.mews-develop.com)" rel=3D"nofollow">http=
s://app.mews-develop.com)</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9777bf2a-825d-44df-83bc-460125c460f0">
<p local-id=3D"8196d55aa252">Enterprise: 9173ac0f-7f88-4f5b-8bba-b310006b0d=
a0 (Madeline's Mews Hotel)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"16fc4a3f-a5b8-4a01-af61-7d610be4a721">
<p local-id=3D"c33f3d4c5f7c">Tooling: chrome-devtools MCP (CDP) =E2=86=92 i=
ts own authenticated Chromium instance. Full DevTools surface used: Emulati=
on (viewport, mobile, touch, UA, networkConditions), Network (list/inspect =
requests), Page (snapshot, screenshot), Runtime (evaluate). Where the page'=
s own form-state was unreachable via UI clicks, I used a <code>value</code>=
-setter shim that bypasses React's controlled-input shadowing and re-dispat=
ches <code>input</code>/<code>change</code>/<code>blur</code> events to coe=
rce the form to commit the new state.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0847a76a-3d63-4a76-83c1-84650fa3e57b">
<p local-id=3D"586518a94be0">This run <strong>supersedes</strong> the parti=
al run earlier in the session. It also corrects two findings from that run =
that were mis-classified.</p></li>
</ul>
