<p local-id=3D"e3fff7b22527">Untestable on this build</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5e5c3421-694e-4346-93ae-03b51df3fd1a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"02b460aa5efe">27 (includes the 11 unreached swipe/undo rows =
+ dataset-thin rows + by-design P15)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b54859db-3316-4ad9-ace7-861b78b0508b">
<td data-local-id=3D"bde44fee-5361-4e6f-be18-4f5082b4b70b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dc9a69062595">Notable corrections to prior session</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ddb068fd-2614-4044-b6c0-8a7890b1f905" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"462bf424b532">3 (AGT-1094 invalid; AGT-1096 mis-framed; AGT-=
1103 closed-as-invalid)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"8f00c80c90ea">The most consequential blockers, by drop-dead =
severity:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"f3e50d61-772a-4119-b514-195e1de23716">
<li local-id=3D"8d29573e-d65d-4895-9dcf-af3f67d02237">
<p local-id=3D"5e561f2c98d0"><strong>P0 =E2=80=94 bookmarkable URLs do NOT =
hydrate the form.</strong> URL params like <code>dateRange.endDateRaw.date=
=3D2026-05-07</code> exist (Apply writes them) but the page on mount falls =
back to today-only and never reads them. A user pasting a filtered URL sees=
 default results, not the URL's results. <em>(New, not in prior session.)</=
em></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"75579284-8f8a-4d1c-85c6-e89ff0a29eb5">
<p local-id=3D"37317eddb8c9"><strong>P0 =E2=80=94 Accept/Reject mutations f=
ire immediately; no Undo affordance anywhere.</strong> Re-confirmed on this=
 build's desktop list, desktop grid, and mobile-emulated drawer. Same as AG=
T-1092 =E2=80=94 still valid.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b31ef078-80df-48b7-af50-dd111144bd0c">
<p local-id=3D"81de6de28e4d"><strong>P0 =E2=80=94 offline / API failure loo=
ks identical to "all reviewed" success state.</strong> The plan promised an=
 error banner; in practice the page renders the green-check empty state whe=
n the dailyDigest GET fails. Users can't tell whether they're offline or fi=
nished. <em>(New.)</em></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d50884ac-a7b9-4aaa-93cd-3b71d7deb3f2">
<p local-id=3D"246f733eed75"><strong>P1 =E2=80=94 SwipeableSuggestionCard i=
s never rendered</strong>, even at viewport=3D375=C3=97667 with <code>mobil=
e:true, hasTouch:true</code> and an iOS Safari UA. The whole Sw1=E2=80=93Sw=
8 / U1=E2=80=93U8 row is unreachable on this build. AGT-1096's "tweener" fr=
aming was a symptom; the real bug is that the swipe layer never engages.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f09627b-4810-4978-9e96-c52fb659ee02">
<p local-id=3D"cd04c3edbf57"><strong>P1 =E2=80=94 Side panel and the filter=
 sidebar lack ARIA dialog / inert semantics.</strong> The panel uses a cust=
om <code>SidePanelWrapper</code> with no <code>role=3D"dialog"</code>, no <=
code>aria-modal</code>. The filter sidebar wrapper has no <code>inert</code=
> and no <code>aria-hidden</code> when the panel is open. Tab order leaks i=
nto a sidebar the user can't see clearly through the panel. AGT-1092's plan=
-referenced "P4 sidebar inert" path is not actually wired up.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"fd8ed1548cdd">The good surprises:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"709b98b4-525f-46c7-aaed-9502898ba46d">
<li local-id=3D"82e4d240-0177-4b59-a023-f8556eaf7f25">
<p local-id=3D"683b55bb7148"><strong>N2/N3 =E2=80=94 mutation-failure recov=
ery actually works.</strong> When <code>POST /smartTasks/{create,reject}</c=
ode> returns 500, the optimistic removal is rolled back and a refetch of th=
e digest is triggered. Cache stays consistent.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b74acb5d-4dc7-4491-8e93-22c038835892">
<p local-id=3D"7beb36587b12"><strong>The card-as-button HTML is fine.</stro=
ng> Prior session's AGT-1094 ("nested buttons") was based on a misread of t=
he a11y tree. The real DOM uses a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> and a sibling=
 <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> of Accept/Reject in grid view, and a <code>&lt;di=
v role=3D"button"&gt;</code> containing them in list view =E2=80=94 neither=
 nests <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> inside <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>.</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"9e16758a-0840-4333-871a-9695e02131c1">
<p local-id=3D"def31b3103ca"><strong>Date-picker </strong><code>+8 day</cod=
e> lockout works correctly (D3).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"55b1945e-3f24-4ce3-b8f3-f61873490ebf">
<p local-id=3D"4434b4a83eaa"><strong>Skeleton states render</strong> during=
 slow loads (E3, observed via Slow 3G emulation: 8 SkeletonCards visible wh=
ile data was in flight).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ba7b3553-3877-4ba1-8bce-cd3f59ad5c67">
<p local-id=3D"c137691f15f7"><strong>Filter state IS persisted in the URL o=
n Apply</strong> =E2=80=94 bookmarkable in principle, even if hydration is =
broken (see #1 above).</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"bbc86ab122e9" id=3D"BlitzTestingDailyDigestwithClaude-Sessi=
onsummary">Session summary</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"54eb9668-4f62-437e-9537-3123ebbf3a27">
<li local-id=3D"4e23f574-f658-415f-8387-3c0e7be13e48">
<p local-id=3D"ebd3d3e54dfd"><strong>Coverage:</strong> 78 of 89 matrix row=
s documented (88%); 38 PASS, 8 FAIL, 6 PARTIAL/dataset-limited, 26 untestab=
le on this build (the unreached 11 =E2=80=94 Sw3=E2=80=93Sw8 and U3=E2=80=
=93U8 =E2=80=94 fall here too because the swipe layer never engages). The 1=
2 "edge cases beyond the matrix" items in the plan were not separately addr=
essed in this run =E2=80=94 gap to call out.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a380e9f1-a5c9-4d21-b00a-56cc0cd3cfa3">
<p local-id=3D"252f99010110"><strong>Highest impact:</strong> the URL-hydra=
tion bug (new) and the offline-as-success state (new) join the existing no-=
Undo bug (re-confirmed) at P0.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"09d9b7c6-f5d8-46f0-a518-b3fd472a46f6">
<p local-id=3D"e5474b4c8742"><strong>The prior session's nested-button find=
ing (AGT-1094) was a false positive</strong> =E2=80=94 the actual HTML is f=
ine. That ticket should be closed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"59711a50-aeea-4f1c-937e-b10f2b8e6261">
<p local-id=3D"00a52279aba2"><strong>The prior session's tweener-viewport f=
inding (AGT-1096) was a symptom of a deeper bug</strong> =E2=80=94 the swip=
e layer never engages at all. The ticket should be re-titled and rescoped.<=
/p></li>
</ul>
